ionstheologie und -praxis in der Frühen Neuzeit und führt andererseits konfessionsspezifische Zentralanliegen vor Augen.  aThe term "mercy seat," coined by Martin Luther, designates the lid of the Old Testament Ark of the Covenant, which Paulus typologically interprets as Jesus Christ in Romans 3:25. This volume examines the multimedial interpretative history of the motif of the mercy seat, which was extremely prominent in the early modern period, and examines to which extent this central topic developed in a process of interconfessional exchange.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aBIldtheologie. 4aBundeslade. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aKirchengeschichte. 4aVersöhnung. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aEarly modern period.  aark.  achurch history.  areconciliation.  atheology of the image.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831107982720 cprintz978311079557840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311079823440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110798234423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110798234/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK